1
00:00:18,585 --> 00:00:22,887
<i> YOU JUST MISSED HIM.</i>
<i> ONLY BEEN GONE</i>
<i> A COUPLE DAYS.</i>

2
00:00:22,956 --> 00:00:24,956
<i>[ Man #2 ]</i>
<i>I'LL CHECK THE DRESSER.</i>

3
00:00:29,563 --> 00:00:31,496
HOW DID HE LOOK?

4
00:00:31,565 --> 00:00:35,033
OH. ABOUT 6'2",
170 POUNDS, I GUESS.

5
00:00:35,102 --> 00:00:37,035
<i> [ Sydney ]</i>
<i> THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEAN.</i>

6
00:00:37,104 --> 00:00:39,838
<i> I MEAN, WAS HE OKAY?</i>
<i> DID HE SEEM IN GOOD HEALTH?</i>

7
00:00:39,907 --> 00:00:44,342
ARE YOU KIDDIN'?
MAN HAD A PHYSIQUE
THE PROS WOULD KILL FOR.

8
00:00:46,313 --> 00:00:51,449
<i> [ Man ] SO, TELL ME, UH,</i>
<i> IF MR. SPITZ WASN'T REALLY</i>
<i> AN ATOMIC ENGINEER,</i>

9
00:00:51,518 --> 00:00:55,186
HOW DID HE STOP THE NUKE PLANT
FROM TURNIN' US
INTO PORK RIND?

10
00:00:55,255 --> 00:00:57,856
MR. SPITZ IS, UM--
A FASCINATING MAN.

11
00:00:57,925 --> 00:00:59,424
OH.

12
00:01:01,362 --> 00:01:05,397
SO, ANY STAB AT
JAROD'S OEDIPAL TRAGEDY,
DR. FREUD?

13
00:01:05,466 --> 00:01:09,134
<i> [ Man ]</i>
<i> JAROD. THAT WAS</i>
<i> HIS FIRST NAME, YEAH.</i>

14
00:01:09,202 --> 00:01:11,135
<i> STRANGE,</i>

15
00:01:11,205 --> 00:01:13,539
BUT YOU'D THINK A GROWN MAN
WITH A LAST NAME OF SPITZ...

16
00:01:13,607 --> 00:01:15,574
<i> WOULD ALREADY KNOW</i>
<i> HOW TO SWIM, WOULDN'T YA?</i>

17
00:01:15,642 --> 00:01:17,575
HE WAS HERE
FOR SWIMMING LESSONS?

18
00:01:17,644 --> 00:01:20,078
HEY, WE ARE THE "Y."

19
00:01:20,147 --> 00:01:22,114
HE WAS
A QUICK LEARNER TOO.

20
00:01:22,182 --> 00:01:24,783
FROM PIKE TO ADVANCED ADULT
IN JUST FIVE WEEKS.

21
00:01:24,852 --> 00:01:28,353
DAY IN, DAY OUT,
SWIMMING WAS ALL HE DID.

22
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:30,488
EXCEPT FOR
THIS PAST WEEK.

23
00:01:30,557 --> 00:01:33,458
HE SPENT EVERY SECOND
IN THE POOL, BUT
HE DIDN'T SWIM A STROKE.

24
00:01:33,527 --> 00:01:35,460
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

25
00:01:35,529 --> 00:01:38,964
FROM THE TIME WE OPENED
IN THE MORNING UNTIL THE
MIDNIGHT CREW CLOSED HER DOWN,

26
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:40,966
HE'D BE THERE
IN THE DEEP END...

27
00:01:41,035 --> 00:01:43,935
TREADING WATER
WITHOUT EVER STOPPING.

28
00:01:44,004 --> 00:01:46,371
JUST TREADING WATER.

29
00:01:48,375 --> 00:01:52,110
I WONDER WHAT
YOUR SCIENCE PROJECT
IS UP TO NOW.

30
00:01:54,348 --> 00:01:57,081
<i>[ Woman Over Radio ]</i>
<i>BANKING TWO-NINER</i>
<i>AND HEADING DOWN.</i>

31
00:01:57,150 --> 00:02:00,419
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>GO IN FOR A CLOSER LOOK.</i>

32
00:02:02,522 --> 00:02:07,192
<i>IT'S SMOKING PRETTY BADLY.</i>
<i>I'LL CALL IN A RESCUE CRAFT.</i>

33
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:09,627
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>SHE'S GOING OVERBOARD.</i>

34
00:02:09,696 --> 00:02:12,831
THERE'S NO TIME!

35
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:15,667
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>JAROD, NO!</i>

36
00:02:34,522 --> 00:02:37,189
<i> COME ON, JAROD.</i>

37
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,393
[ Coughing ]

38
00:02:41,462 --> 00:02:44,763
HELLO. MY NAME IS JAROD.

39
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:47,232
YOU'RE GONNA BE JUST FINE.

40
00:02:49,236 --> 00:02:52,738
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>

41
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:48,059
<i> MISS PARKER,</i>
<i> YOU HAVE A FAX.</i>

42
00:04:03,377 --> 00:04:06,777
[ Together ]
1,324.

43
00:04:06,846 --> 00:04:11,282
<i> [ Door Opens, Closes ]</i>
VERY GOOD, GIRLS,
AND ABSOLUTELY CORRECT.

44
00:04:11,351 --> 00:04:13,351
SYDNEY, NOW!

45
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:21,759
YOUR THEATRICS
UPSET THE CHILDREN.

46
00:04:21,828 --> 00:04:24,062
SAVE THE MR. ROGERS, SYD.

47
00:04:24,130 --> 00:04:27,031
I SET UP A TEXT SESSION
WITH BROOTS SO THAT
HE CAN HELP US TRACK JAROD.

48
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:30,235
I THINK THAT TAKES PRECEDENCE
OVER THING 1 AND THING 2.

49
00:04:30,304 --> 00:04:34,138
BROOTS'S TECHNOLOGY ISN'T GOING
TO HELP US TRACK A CHAMELEON.

50
00:04:34,208 --> 00:04:37,141
JAROD CHANGES COLOR.
HE BLENDS IN.

51
00:04:37,211 --> 00:04:39,144
WE'LL GET CLOSE
WHEN HE LETS US.

52
00:04:39,212 --> 00:04:42,614
PATIENCE, PARKER.
WE NEED PATIENCE.

53
00:04:42,683 --> 00:04:45,750
SYD, PATIENCE MAY BE
A SOOTHING CATCHALL...

54
00:04:45,819 --> 00:04:48,153
FOR THE POTATO HEADS
IN PSYCHOGENIC SERVICES.

55
00:04:48,221 --> 00:04:52,190
BUT MY FATHER AND
THE BOYS IN THE TOWER
EQUATE PATIENCE WITH FAILURE.

56
00:04:52,258 --> 00:04:54,192
BUT JAROD IS A PRETENDER.

57
00:04:54,260 --> 00:04:57,028
HE CAN BECOME
ANYONE HE WANTS TO BE.

58
00:04:57,097 --> 00:04:59,598
WE'LL NEVER CATCH HIM WITH
ONE OF BROOTS'S PHONE TAPS.

59
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,800
THAT'S WHAT THEY SAID
ABOUT THE UNABOMBER, SYD.

60
00:05:01,869 --> 00:05:04,136
AND HOW DID THEY CATCH
THAT WHACKED-OUT PRODIGY?

61
00:05:04,204 --> 00:05:06,138
A LETTER TO MOMMY.

62
00:05:06,206 --> 00:05:09,174
IT'S THE SMART ONES
WHO ALWAYS DO SOMETHING STUPID.

63
00:05:09,242 --> 00:05:12,677
LET'S USE THE STAIRS.
IT'S ONLY THREE FLIGHTS UP.
COME ON.

64
00:05:14,848 --> 00:05:17,315
STOP NURTURING, SYDNEY.
[ Bell Dings ]

65
00:05:17,384 --> 00:05:20,952
HELL, IT'S BEEN 20 YEARS.
I DON'T HAVE ANY PROBLEM
RIDING THIS ELEVATOR.

66
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:23,020
YOU SHOULDN'T EITHER.

67
00:05:30,731 --> 00:05:32,664
YOUR MOTHER
WAS A SPECIAL PERSON.

68
00:05:32,733 --> 00:05:34,999
MY MOTHER WAS WEAK. PERIOD.

69
00:05:35,068 --> 00:05:39,070
SHE COULDN'T HANDLE
THE PRESSURES OF S.I.S.
OR THIS PLACE.

70
00:05:39,139 --> 00:05:41,373
I DON'T HAVE
THAT PROBLEM.

71
00:05:43,477 --> 00:05:46,478
ONLY THING THAT
EVER BOTHERED ME WAS--

72
00:05:46,546 --> 00:05:48,613
WHY IN AN ELEVATOR?

73
00:05:48,682 --> 00:05:51,916
THEY GO UP,
THEY GO DOWN.

74
00:05:51,985 --> 00:05:54,218
THEY END UP NOWHERE.

75
00:05:55,989 --> 00:05:59,691
IT'S AMAZING HOW
A SINGLE BULLET
CAN CHANGE YOUR LIFE.

76
00:06:01,561 --> 00:06:04,028
IF YOU EVER WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT--

77
00:06:07,334 --> 00:06:10,034
CORRECT ME IF I'M WRONG, SYDNEY,
BUT WASN'T MY MOTHER'S
SESSION WITH YOU...

78
00:06:10,103 --> 00:06:13,905
ONE OF THE LAST THINGS SHE DID
BEFORE SHE GOT ON THIS ELEVATOR?

79
00:06:13,973 --> 00:06:16,140
NO, THANKS.
[ Bell Dings ]

80
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:19,911
[ Chuckles ]
SYDNEY, I'LL TAKE
MY OWN CHANCES.

81
00:06:29,355 --> 00:06:31,356
[ Chattering ]

82
00:06:33,827 --> 00:06:36,928
MARTHA.
GOOD MORNING.

83
00:06:36,997 --> 00:06:41,299
YOU LOOK WAY TOO RESTED TO BE
STAYING IN COAST GUARD HOUSING.
I LIVE OFF-BASE.

84
00:06:41,368 --> 00:06:44,402
IT TOOK THREE YEARS
AND A HUSBAND TO GET ME
OUT OF THE IRON COT.

85
00:06:44,471 --> 00:06:47,238
- HOW'D YOU SWING IT?
- I FORGED MY TRANSFER PAPERS.

86
00:06:47,307 --> 00:06:50,142
[ Laughs ]
OH.

87
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:55,180
MARTHA, ARE YOU OKAY?

88
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:59,617
YEAH, IT'S, UH,
BAD SUSHI.

89
00:06:59,686 --> 00:07:02,620
IS THERE ANY OTHER KIND?
LIEUTENANT CAMPBELL.
GOOD MORNING.

90
00:07:02,689 --> 00:07:04,622
GOOD MORNING.
I'M GLAD I CAUGHT YOU.

91
00:07:04,691 --> 00:07:06,624
I WANTED YOU TO MEET
MY LIEUTENANT COMMANDER,
PAUL BILSON.

92
00:07:06,693 --> 00:07:09,994
PLEASURE TO MEET YOU, SIR.
WORD IS YOU DID SOME PRETTY
GOOD WORK OUT THERE YESTERDAY.

93
00:07:10,063 --> 00:07:12,163
HEARD YOU EVEN PLUCKED A VICTIM
OUT OF THE SOUP.

94
00:07:12,231 --> 00:07:14,466
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
I TOOK THOSE SWIM LESSONS
AT THE "Y."

95
00:07:14,535 --> 00:07:19,838
[ Laughing ]
I WISH ALL MY TRANSFERS HAD YOUR
HUMILITY, NOT TO MENTION TALENT.

96
00:07:19,906 --> 00:07:23,407
<i>COMMANDER POWELL, I WAS HOPING</i>
<i>TO GET A FEW MINUTES</i>
<i>REGARDING MY RANK REVIEW.</i>

97
00:07:23,476 --> 00:07:26,310
- WELL, ALL RANK REVIEWS
GO THROUGH THE L.C.
-<i> I KNOW. IT'S ON MY DESK.</i>

98
00:07:26,379 --> 00:07:29,280
- I'LL GET ON IT A.S.A.P.
- THANK YOU, SIR.

99
00:07:29,349 --> 00:07:33,118
<i> WELL, I'LL LEAVE YOU IN</i>
<i> ABLER HANDS, LT. CAMPBELL.</i>

100
00:07:33,187 --> 00:07:34,819
THANK YOU, SIR.

101
00:07:34,888 --> 00:07:38,656
<i> WELL, THE REAL QUESTION IS,</i>
<i> WHAT KIND OF SEA LEGS</i>
<i> DO YOU HAVE?</i>

102
00:07:38,725 --> 00:07:40,691
AS YOU KNOW,
ANYBODY CAN FLY,
RIGHT, POOLE?

103
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,927
A KITE MAYBE, SIR.

104
00:07:45,699 --> 00:07:48,333
LIEUTENANT.

105
00:07:48,401 --> 00:07:52,337
GOOD MORNING, L.C.
HEY, GOT THE<i> CHRISTI</i>
PURRIN' LIKE A KITTEN.

106
00:07:52,405 --> 00:07:55,506
I DON'T TRUST THAT OLD NAG.
I'LL TAKE THE 45.
YES, SIR!

107
00:07:55,575 --> 00:07:58,543
COMMANDER POWELL LIKES HIS MEN
TO BE REAL SAILORS.
YOU UP FOR SOME SEA DUTY?

108
00:07:58,612 --> 00:08:01,046
AS READY AS
I'LL EVER BE, SIR.
JAVI, WE'RE WAITING!

109
00:08:01,114 --> 00:08:03,280
<i>[ Javi ]</i>
<i>RUMBLE BASE ALPHA SIGNING OFF.</i>

110
00:08:03,349 --> 00:08:06,417
HAVEN'T YOU EVER HEARD
OF THE INTERNET? E-MAIL?

111
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:10,021
- I'M A PURIST.
I CRAVE STATIC.
- YOU COMIN'?

112
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:12,090
YEAH.

113
00:08:16,095 --> 00:08:18,029
HI. JAROD CAMPBELL.
JAVI PADILLA.

114
00:08:18,097 --> 00:08:20,064
NICE TO MEET YOU.
IS BILSON ALWAYS
IN SUCH A HURRY?

115
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:22,133
ONLY WHEN THE OCEAN CALLS.

116
00:08:25,739 --> 00:08:29,007
COMMANDER POWELL TELLS ME
YOU'VE BEEN RUNNING
ICEBREAKERS OFF KATIMA BAY.

117
00:08:29,076 --> 00:08:32,910
GREAT LAKES?
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME THIS WAS
A FRESHWATER BOY, SIR.

118
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:35,479
AH, GIVE ME A BREAK.
AT LEAST I TRANSFERRED
TO THE UNIT...

119
00:08:35,548 --> 00:08:37,949
WITH THE BEST S.A.R. RECORD
IN THE GUARD.

120
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:42,420
YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT. WE CONDUCTED
178 SEARCH-AND-RESCUES
LAST YEAR ALONE.

121
00:08:42,488 --> 00:08:45,089
<i>WHOO!</i>

122
00:08:49,662 --> 00:08:51,696
<i> [ Bilson ]</i>
<i> LOOKS LIKE A 42-80 TO ME.</i>

123
00:08:51,765 --> 00:08:55,199
IT'S LISTING
ABOUT THREE DEGREES.
ABANDONED?

124
00:08:55,268 --> 00:08:58,336
<i> [ Bilson ] THAT'S MY GUESS.</i>
<i> JAVI, CALL IT IN.</i>

125
00:08:58,405 --> 00:09:00,638
JAROD, CHECK IT OUT.

126
00:09:02,409 --> 00:09:05,076
<i> HELLO?</i>

127
00:09:05,145 --> 00:09:07,779
IT'S THE COAST GUARD.

128
00:09:07,848 --> 00:09:10,849
IS ANYBODY HERE?
HELLO?

129
00:09:12,819 --> 00:09:16,354
WHOA, NOW, SIR.
NOBODY'S HERE TO HURT YOU.

130
00:09:16,422 --> 00:09:18,423
[ Both Laughing ]

131
00:09:18,491 --> 00:09:21,192
OH, HELL.

132
00:09:21,261 --> 00:09:24,362
<i> ROY ABBOTT, SAY HELLO</i>
<i> TO LT. CAMPBELL.</i>

133
00:09:24,431 --> 00:09:27,065
<i> HI. CALL ME JAROD.</i>

134
00:09:27,134 --> 00:09:28,900
GET OFF MY BOAT.

135
00:09:28,969 --> 00:09:31,268
AH, COME ON, ROY. IS THAT
ANY WAY TO TREAT THE NEW GUY?

136
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:34,105
SIR.

137
00:09:34,174 --> 00:09:38,276
YOUR STORES APPEAR TO BE LOW,
AND YOU ALSO APPEAR
TO BE TAKING ON WATER.

138
00:09:38,345 --> 00:09:42,913
WHY DON'T YOU LET US
TOW YOU ASHORE
SO WE CAN HELP YOU RESUPPLY?

139
00:09:42,982 --> 00:09:46,017
NOTHIN' I NEED OVER THERE.
I'M FINE WHERE I AM.

140
00:09:46,086 --> 00:09:49,120
<i>[ Bilson ]</i>
<i>MR. ABBOTT,</i>
<i>THE COMMANDER DID NOT AGREE.</i>

141
00:09:49,189 --> 00:09:54,124
YOU HAVE ONE WEEK TO COME IN,
OR WE'RE AUTHORIZED
TO BRING YOU IN, SIR.

142
00:09:54,193 --> 00:09:56,794
IT'S FOR YOUR OWN GOOD,
MR. ABBOTT.

143
00:10:01,802 --> 00:10:06,037
<i> [ Telephone Ringing ]</i>
SYDNEY.

144
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:09,474
WELL, I'M SURPRISED
YOU'RE NOT OUT MAKING ROUNDS
DOWN CORRIDOR 15.

145
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:13,444
<i>EVEN A PSYCHIATRIST</i>
<i>NEEDS A DAY OFF.</i>

146
00:10:13,513 --> 00:10:16,781
AND ALL THIS TIME,
I THOUGHT YOUR INTEREST IN ME
WAS PURELY PATERNAL.

147
00:10:16,850 --> 00:10:19,784
I UNDERSTAND LEARNING TO SWIM,
BUT AREN'T YOU A LITTLE OLD...

148
00:10:19,852 --> 00:10:22,119
TO BE PLAYING
WITH BATHTUB TOYS?

149
00:10:22,188 --> 00:10:25,522
WELL, IT'S CERTAINLY BETTER
THAN THE KIND OF PLAYTIME
YOU FOISTED UPON ME.

150
00:10:25,591 --> 00:10:27,858
IT'S FUNNY.

151
00:10:27,927 --> 00:10:29,961
I CAN'T SEE THEIR FACES.

152
00:10:30,029 --> 00:10:34,232
BUT THEIR EYES--
THEY WON'T STOP
STARING AT ME.

153
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:37,735
<i> WHOSE EYES, JAROD?</i>
I DON'T KNOW.

154
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:40,538
DEAD EYES.

155
00:10:40,607 --> 00:10:42,540
EYES OF PEOPLE
THAT AREN'T ALIVE TODAY...

156
00:10:42,609 --> 00:10:44,809
BECAUSE OF HOW YOU EXPLOITED
MY SIMULATIONS.

157
00:10:46,012 --> 00:10:50,382
AND NOW, YOU WANT
TO RIGHT THOSE WRONGS...

158
00:10:50,450 --> 00:10:52,684
BY USING YOUR GIFT
AS AN AVENGING ANGEL.

159
00:10:52,752 --> 00:10:55,186
-<i> IS THAT IT?</i>
- SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

160
00:10:55,255 --> 00:10:57,722
[ Sydney ]
THEN WHY ARE YOU CALLING?

161
00:10:59,459 --> 00:11:02,460
I WANTED TO KNOW IF--

162
00:11:02,529 --> 00:11:05,230
IF JAROD WAS MY REAL NAME.

163
00:11:05,298 --> 00:11:09,233
I THINK IT IS. AT LEAST,
THAT'S WHAT I WAS TOLD.

164
00:11:12,371 --> 00:11:15,273
THANK YOU, SYDNEY.

165
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:18,376
DON'T HANG UP.

166
00:11:18,445 --> 00:11:20,311
I'M WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

167
00:11:20,379 --> 00:11:23,848
IF YOU'RE SO WORRIED ABOUT ME,
WHY DON'T YOU GO
TO THE AUTHORITIES?

168
00:11:23,917 --> 00:11:27,218
YOU KNOW I CAN'T DO THAT.
WHY?

169
00:11:27,287 --> 00:11:29,788
BECAUSE YOU LOVE ME?

170
00:11:29,856 --> 00:11:32,423
OR BECAUSE YOU'RE AFRAID
OF WHAT I KNOW?

171
00:11:32,492 --> 00:11:36,694
JAROD, IF THOSE PEOPLE
FROM THE BELTWAY
FIND OUT WHAT YOU HAVE,

172
00:11:36,763 --> 00:11:38,929
I WON'T BE ABLE
TO PROTECT YOU.

173
00:11:38,998 --> 00:11:42,100
IF THEY FIND OUT
WHAT I HAVE,

174
00:11:42,169 --> 00:11:44,702
YOU WON'T BE ABLE
TO PROTECT YOURSELVES.

175
00:11:44,771 --> 00:11:47,405
THOSE D.S.A.'s
CONTAIN MY WORK.

176
00:11:47,474 --> 00:11:51,208
NO, SYDNEY.
THEY CONTAIN MY LIFE.

177
00:11:51,277 --> 00:11:53,278
GOOD-BYE.

178
00:11:54,581 --> 00:11:56,581
[ Sighs ]

179
00:11:58,150 --> 00:12:00,485
WE GOT YOU, GENIUS.

180
00:12:03,990 --> 00:12:06,223
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>NOW THIS IS VERY INTERESTING.</i>

181
00:12:07,860 --> 00:12:10,495
YOU MEAN SOMEBODY
ACTUALLY MANUFACTURES...

182
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:13,231
IMITATION CANINE FECES?

183
00:12:13,299 --> 00:12:16,066
YEP. ONLY THEY COULDN'T
FIT ALL THAT ON THE LABEL,

184
00:12:16,136 --> 00:12:18,402
SO THEY JUST CALL IT
FAKE DOG POOP.

185
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:21,873
OH.

186
00:12:21,942 --> 00:12:25,642
AND WHY EXACTLY WOULD
SOMEBODY WANT FAKE DOG POOP?

187
00:12:27,013 --> 00:12:28,946
'CAUSE IT'S FUNNY.

188
00:12:31,350 --> 00:12:36,421
- OH.
- NO, I MEAN THE WHITE ONES.
YEAH.

189
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:38,490
<i>THANK YOU.</i>

190
00:12:42,195 --> 00:12:44,161
IT IS FUNNY.

191
00:12:52,172 --> 00:12:56,306
I GOT THE WHITE ONES, MOMMY.
THOSE WERE HIS FAVORITES.

192
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:56,700
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>BROOTS TRACED JAROD'S CALL</i>
<i>BACK TO THIS Y.M.C.A.</i>

193
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:00,771
GET HIM!

194
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:04,141
HEY, HEY, HEY!
I AIN'T DONE NOTHIN'.
I AIN'T DONE NOTHIN'.

195
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:06,510
WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN THIS ROOM?

196
00:14:06,579 --> 00:14:09,013
I AIN'T TRESPASSIN'. NO.
THIS GUY GAVE ME THE ROOM.

197
00:14:09,082 --> 00:14:11,115
IS THIS THE MAN?
<i>YEAH, THAT-THAT'S HIM.</i>

198
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:14,151
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
HE CONDUCTS THE PHILHARMONIC.
MM-HMM.

199
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:16,954
<i> AND-AND HE GIVES ME</i>
<i> SIX MONTHS' FREE RENT</i>
<i> JUST TO TRANSFER HIS CALLS.</i>

200
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:20,358
<i>AND YOU KNOW WHAT?</i>
<i>HE SAYS HE LIKES</i>
<i>TO TRAVEL A LOT.</i>

201
00:14:23,296 --> 00:14:25,329
SHUT UP, SYDNEY.

202
00:14:26,566 --> 00:14:28,900
<i>♪♪ [ Opera Over Radio ]</i>

203
00:14:28,968 --> 00:14:33,137
♪♪ [ Whistling ]
<i> GOOD MORNING, MR. ABBOTT.</i>

204
00:14:33,206 --> 00:14:35,340
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

205
00:14:35,408 --> 00:14:39,477
I DON'T KNOW.
I WAS JUST PASSING THROUGH.

206
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:42,313
PERMISSION TO COME ABOARD?

207
00:14:42,382 --> 00:14:44,415
GRANTED.

208
00:14:53,459 --> 00:14:55,392
<i> MAGDELINE'S</i> A PRETTY LADY.

209
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:59,863
HOW DO YOU KNOW MAGDELINE?

210
00:14:59,932 --> 00:15:01,865
I WAS TALKING ABOUT YOUR BOAT.

211
00:15:04,036 --> 00:15:06,571
IS THAT YOUR WIFE?

212
00:15:06,639 --> 00:15:09,840
COULD'VE BEEN.
PROBABLY WOULD'VE.

213
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:12,710
I NEVER ASKED HER.

214
00:15:16,349 --> 00:15:19,450
DO YOU THINK THE DUTCHMAN
EVER FOUND HIS LOST LOVE?

215
00:15:19,519 --> 00:15:22,253
<i>WHAT?</i>

216
00:15:22,322 --> 00:15:25,389
<i> THE OPERA</i>
<i> YOU WERE LISTENING TO.</i>
<i> WAGNER'S</i> DUTCHMAN.

217
00:15:25,458 --> 00:15:28,626
<i> THAT'S THE STORY.</i>
<i> I ALWAYS WONDERED...</i>

218
00:15:28,694 --> 00:15:30,861
IF HE EVER SEARCHED
FOR HIS LOVE...

219
00:15:30,931 --> 00:15:34,097
OR SPENT THE REST OF HIS DAYS
FLOATING AROUND ON
THAT GHOST SHIP.

220
00:15:34,166 --> 00:15:36,267
I NEVER REALLY
GAVE IT MUCH THOUGHT.

221
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:40,971
IT'S NOT EASY WONDERING
IF SOMEONE YOU LOVE
IS STILL OUT THERE.

222
00:15:46,813 --> 00:15:49,313
I AIN'T MOVIN' MY BOAT.

223
00:15:49,381 --> 00:15:51,448
I'M NOT ASKING YOU TO.

224
00:15:54,921 --> 00:15:57,555
I'M JUST BORROWING THE UNIFORM.

225
00:15:57,623 --> 00:16:00,624
<i> I BROUGHT YOU SOME SUPPLIES</i>
<i> FROM TOWN.</i>

226
00:16:00,692 --> 00:16:03,493
<i> I'LL TRADE YOU FOR...</i>

227
00:16:04,597 --> 00:16:06,530
THIS CHEST YOU CARVED.

228
00:16:06,599 --> 00:16:11,368
THROW IN SOME CANDLES
NEXT TIME YOU PASS,
YOU GOT YOURSELF A DEAL.

229
00:16:12,605 --> 00:16:16,073
DONE. THANKS.

230
00:16:18,277 --> 00:16:21,111
DO YOU EVER LISTEN
TO MOZART, MR. ABBOTT?

231
00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:23,881
THE MAGIC FLUTE?

232
00:16:23,949 --> 00:16:26,816
I LIKE THIS ONE FINE.
IT'S ALL I NEED.

233
00:16:26,885 --> 00:16:30,320
I WAS ALLOWED TO LISTEN TO IT
ONCE WHEN I WAS A CHILD.

234
00:16:32,257 --> 00:16:36,326
I'D CLOSE MY EYES,
AND IN MY MIND...

235
00:16:36,395 --> 00:16:38,996
I BECAME AN EAGLE.

236
00:16:39,064 --> 00:16:44,502
I COULD GO ANYWHERE,
DO ANYTHING.

237
00:16:44,570 --> 00:16:47,137
NOTHING COULD STOP ME.

238
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:52,976
MAYBE MOZART KNEW SOMETHING
THAT WAGNER DIDN'T.

239
00:16:56,281 --> 00:16:58,849
I AIN'T MOVIN' MY BOAT.

240
00:17:05,358 --> 00:17:07,658
LT. CAMPBELL,
EVEN ON ROUTINE PATROL,

241
00:17:07,727 --> 00:17:10,193
I EXPECT YOUR EYES ON THE DECK.

242
00:17:10,263 --> 00:17:12,296
THIS IS A HELICOPTER,
NOT A LIBRARY.

243
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:16,567
TRYING TO ORIENT MYSELF
TO THE WEST COAST
OCEAN SEARCH PATTERNS.

244
00:17:16,635 --> 00:17:18,635
TELL YOU WHAT.
I WILL BUY YOU LUNCH...

245
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:21,572
IF YOU LET ME PICK YOUR BRAIN
ABOUT SOME OF THESE
OLD SEARCHES.

246
00:17:21,641 --> 00:17:25,408
AS LONG AS IT'S NOT SUSHI.

247
00:17:25,477 --> 00:17:27,444
GREAT. I DON'T WANT
COMMANDER POWELL...

248
00:17:27,513 --> 00:17:30,714
TO TAG ME "FRESHWATER BOY"
ON MY RANK REVIEW.

249
00:17:30,783 --> 00:17:33,984
WAIT A MINUTE.

250
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:37,154
YOU'VE BEEN HERE THREE DAYS,
AND YOU'RE GETTING
A RANK REVIEW?

251
00:17:38,957 --> 00:17:42,826
OH, GREAT!
ALL I NEED IS ANOTHER GUY
IN THIS OPERATION...

252
00:17:42,894 --> 00:17:46,329
<i>ELBOWING FOR ROOM</i>
<i>ON THE LADDER.</i>
WHEN ARE YOU DUE?

253
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:49,867
I SHOULD'VE MADE L.C.
MONTHS AGO,

254
00:17:49,935 --> 00:17:51,769
BUT COMMANDER POWELL
KEEPS PUTTING IT OFF.

255
00:17:51,837 --> 00:17:56,506
NOT YOUR PROMOTION.
YOUR BABY.

256
00:17:56,575 --> 00:18:02,112
I'D SAY FROM YOUR NAUSEA
AND YOUR SORE BACK,
YOU'RE ABOUT NINE WEEKS.

257
00:18:04,050 --> 00:18:08,251
MY HUSBAND DOESN'T EVEN KNOW.
WHAT ARE YOU,
A PART-TIME OBSTETRICIAN?

258
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:10,921
NO, BUT I WAS
A MIDWIFE ONCE.

259
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:12,923
YOU HAVEN'T TOLD
THE COMMANDER YET, HAVE YOU?

260
00:18:12,992 --> 00:18:16,726
HELL NO! IF POWELL
OR ANYONE ELSE AROUND HERE
FINDS OUT ABOUT THIS,

261
00:18:16,795 --> 00:18:19,096
I CAN KISS AWAY
MY CHANCES AT L.C.

262
00:18:19,165 --> 00:18:22,399
YOUR SECRET'S SAFE WITH ME.

263
00:18:22,468 --> 00:18:24,568
<i>WELL, BROOTS, WHAT HAPPENED?</i>

264
00:18:24,636 --> 00:18:26,971
I'M BACKTRACKING HIS CALL
THROUGH THE OTHER PHONE.

265
00:18:27,039 --> 00:18:29,639
ALL I KNOW RIGHT NOW
IS THAT THEY'RE ALL
INTERNATIONAL LANDLINES.

266
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:32,142
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THAT WAS POSSIBLE.
HOW LONG TO TRACE IT?

267
00:18:32,211 --> 00:18:34,211
UH, THAT'S HARD TO SAY.

268
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:38,349
I MEAN, JAROD'S METHOD
IS SO BASIC, SO SIMPLE.

269
00:18:38,417 --> 00:18:41,018
UH, 20--
24 HOURS.

270
00:18:41,087 --> 00:18:43,087
YOU HAVE 12.

271
00:18:44,857 --> 00:18:47,591
I CAN DO IT IN EIGHT.

272
00:18:48,727 --> 00:18:50,661
THE KING FILE?

273
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:53,097
YOU CERTAINLY PICKED
A SENSITIVE ONE.

274
00:18:53,165 --> 00:18:55,398
IT'S ALL DOWNHILL
AFTER THIS.

275
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:58,001
YOU-YOU SHOULD TALK
TO BILSON.
THIS WAS HIS BABY.

276
00:18:58,070 --> 00:19:00,771
<i>HOW SO?</i>
WELL, IT HAPPENED DURING HIS
REGULAR TUESDAY NIGHT PATROL.

277
00:19:00,839 --> 00:19:03,273
SO, BILSON WAS IN CHARGE.

278
00:19:03,341 --> 00:19:07,410
IT WAS A TOUGH ONE TOO.
NO ONE WAS SURE
HOW KING'S BOAT WENT DOWN.

279
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:11,515
NEVER DID FIND IT.
THIS ONE WAS PARTICULARLY SAD.

280
00:19:11,583 --> 00:19:16,753
CORONER SAID TOM KING
TREADED WATER A DAY AND A HALF
BEFORE HE DROWNED.

281
00:19:16,821 --> 00:19:19,356
<i> FOR AN S.A.R. TEAM</i>
<i> THAT'S COME UP EMPTY,</i>

282
00:19:19,425 --> 00:19:21,358
THAT'S THE KIND OF NEWS
THAT HURTS THE MOST.

283
00:19:21,426 --> 00:19:23,860
THIS REPORT SAYS THAT THE SEARCH
PATTERNS WERE BASED...

284
00:19:23,930 --> 00:19:27,631
ON WATER CURRENT INFORMATION
PROVIDED BY DIRECTIONAL BUOYS.

285
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:30,767
YEP.
I DROPPED THEM MYSELF.
HERE.

286
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:32,769
PILCHER'S POINT.

287
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:35,039
THAT'S THE AREA
TOM KING WAS KNOWN
TO HAVE BEEN FISHING IN.

288
00:19:35,107 --> 00:19:38,942
SO BILSON DEPLOYED
STANDARD GRID SEARCHES
SOUTHEAST OF THAT POINT?

289
00:19:39,010 --> 00:19:43,480
THAT'S S.O.P. YOU SEEM
TO BE FOLLOWING THIS FINE.
WHAT IS THE MATTER?

290
00:19:43,549 --> 00:19:45,315
ACCORDING TO
SATELLITE MONITORING,

291
00:19:45,384 --> 00:19:50,120
THE D.F. BUOYS INDICATED
THAT THE CURRENT
WAS MOVING SOUTHWEST.

292
00:20:14,813 --> 00:20:18,815
YOU'RE DOING IT WRONG.
HMM?

293
00:20:18,884 --> 00:20:21,184
DIDN'T YOU EVER
EAT COOKIES AS A KID?

294
00:20:21,253 --> 00:20:24,721
THEY DIDN'T HAVE COOKIES
WHERE I GREW UP.

295
00:20:24,790 --> 00:20:26,823
WHERE'D YOU GROW UP-- MARS?

296
00:20:26,891 --> 00:20:28,592
SORT OF.

297
00:20:31,163 --> 00:20:35,532
FIRST,
YOU TWIST THE COOKIE,

298
00:20:35,601 --> 00:20:40,838
SO THE TOP COMES OFF
LIKE A LITTLE LID.

299
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:43,907
THEN, YOU GET
ALL THE WHITE STUFF OFF.

300
00:20:43,975 --> 00:20:47,844
I PICK IT WITH MY TEETH,
BUT YOU CAN SCRAPE IT
OR LICK IT.

301
00:20:54,186 --> 00:20:56,786
THEN WHAT DO YOU DO
WITH THE BROWN PART?

302
00:20:56,855 --> 00:20:58,755
GROWN-UPS PUT IT
IN ICE CREAM.

303
00:20:58,824 --> 00:21:00,924
WHY DON'T THEY JUST SELL
THE WHITE STUFF?

304
00:21:00,993 --> 00:21:03,293
IT WOULDN'T BE ANY FUN.

305
00:21:03,362 --> 00:21:05,362
HMM.

306
00:21:11,303 --> 00:21:13,237
YOUR MOM WORKS HARD.

307
00:21:16,175 --> 00:21:20,377
SINCE MY DAD DIED,
THAT'S ALL SHE DOES.

308
00:21:22,213 --> 00:21:25,482
HE'S WITH ST. ANDREW--
THE ONE FOR FISHERMEN.

309
00:21:26,585 --> 00:21:30,620
I GOT MY DAD A STATUE
OF HIM AT CHURCH.

310
00:21:30,689 --> 00:21:34,324
IT WAS ON HIS BOAT.
THEY NEVER FOUND THAT.

311
00:21:36,828 --> 00:21:41,664
IT'S HARD TO LOSE A PARENT.
I KNOW.

312
00:21:43,569 --> 00:21:45,936
WHAT PART DO YOU MISS
THE MOST?

313
00:21:49,108 --> 00:21:51,108
MY MOM'S SMILE.

314
00:22:01,086 --> 00:22:03,820
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>
<i>I CAN'T FIGURE IT OUT!</i>
<i>[ Sydney ] YOU HAVE TO.</i>

315
00:22:03,889 --> 00:22:06,523
HOW MUCH OXYGEN IS LEFT?

316
00:22:06,592 --> 00:22:08,658
LESS THAN 48 HOURS.

317
00:22:08,727 --> 00:22:11,361
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>
<i>WELL, WHAT CAUSED THE EXPLOSION?</i>

318
00:22:11,430 --> 00:22:14,698
WE DON'T KNOW!
FUEL.

319
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:24,174
OXYGEN.

320
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:28,779
THERE'S NOTHING
THAT CAN SAVE US!

321
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:32,415
IT'S YOUR DUTY
TO SAVE YOUR CREW!
NO! I CAN'T DO IT!

322
00:22:32,484 --> 00:22:36,319
YOU SHUT DOWN NOW,
YOU ALL DIE!

323
00:22:36,388 --> 00:22:39,589
[ Sighs ]
COME ON, JAROD! THINK!

324
00:22:41,460 --> 00:22:44,627
[ Young Jarod ]
WAIT! WAIT!
I'VE GOT IT! I'VE GOT IT!

325
00:22:44,696 --> 00:22:48,264
I CAN USE THE GRAVITATIONAL
PULL OF THE MOON
TO HELP GET US BACK.

326
00:22:51,903 --> 00:22:56,840
VERY GOOD, JAROD.
I KNEW YOU WOULD SAVE THEM
IF YOU WANTED TO.

327
00:23:02,847 --> 00:23:05,515
THEY DIDN'T WANT
TO SAVE TOM KING.

328
00:23:07,685 --> 00:23:09,752
THEY WANTED HIM TO DIE.

329
00:23:15,260 --> 00:23:17,628
<i>[ Telephone Ringing ]</i>

330
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,134
WHAT?

331
00:23:24,202 --> 00:23:28,004
OH! I INTENTIONALLY WAKE YOU
IN YOUR DEEPEST SLEEP PHASE,

332
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:31,641
AND ALL I GET
IS A LIFELESS "WHAT"?
[ Sighs ]

333
00:23:31,710 --> 00:23:34,978
YOU WANT WIT,
READ NOEL COWARD.

334
00:23:35,047 --> 00:23:37,214
<i> WHAT TIME IS IT</i>
<i> WHERE YOU ARE?</i>

335
00:23:37,282 --> 00:23:41,318
CUTE.
NOT FUNNY, BUT CUTE.

336
00:23:41,386 --> 00:23:46,890
YOU'RE MAKING HOUSE CALLS NOW.
I'M HONORED.

337
00:23:46,958 --> 00:23:49,726
WELL, I WAS FEELING
A LITTLE GUILTY ABOUT
MY VIRTUAL PHONE GAME.

338
00:23:49,795 --> 00:23:53,563
YOU KNOW, I REALLY
SHOULD TAPE THIS TO REPLAY
AT THE CHRISTMAS PARTY.

339
00:23:53,632 --> 00:23:56,399
YOU'LL BE THERE, YOU KNOW,
REST ASSURED.

340
00:23:56,468 --> 00:24:00,337
I'M NOT RESTING MUCH
AT ALL THESE DAYS.
BREAKING MY HEART.

341
00:24:00,405 --> 00:24:04,340
SO, JAROD,

342
00:24:04,410 --> 00:24:06,876
WHY THE Y.M.C.A.?

343
00:24:06,945 --> 00:24:10,647
I WAS WATCHING RETRO NIGHT
ON VH1, AND
THEY WERE DOING THE '70s,

344
00:24:10,715 --> 00:24:12,882
WHICH, AS YOU KNOW,
I MISSED.

345
00:24:12,952 --> 00:24:16,686
THERE WAS THIS SINGING GROUP
THAT WAS EXTOLLING THE VIRTUES
OF STAYING AT THE "Y."

346
00:24:16,755 --> 00:24:19,188
SO, HERE I AM.

347
00:24:19,258 --> 00:24:22,225
CUTE.
NOT FUNNY, BUT CUTE.

348
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:27,197
DID YOU KNOW THAT
THEY MAKE FAKE DOG POOP?

349
00:24:27,266 --> 00:24:31,067
IT'S AMAZING--
HOW IT APPEARS TO BE ONE THING,

350
00:24:31,136 --> 00:24:33,537
BUT IT'S REALLY
SOMETHING COMPLETELY DIFFERENT.
<i>[ Clatters On Table ]</i>

351
00:24:33,606 --> 00:24:36,172
AND I SHOULD CARE BECAUSE--

352
00:24:36,242 --> 00:24:39,076
WELL, THIS SORT OF THING
COULD BE A REAL MONEYMAKER
FOR THE CENTRE.

353
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:41,811
BESIDES, ISN'T IT
THE PERFECT METAPHOR...

354
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:45,382
FOR THE WAY YOUR FATHER
AND THE CENTRE
DISTORT THE TRUTH?

355
00:24:45,451 --> 00:24:51,354
AND WHAT TRUTH IS THAT, JAROD?
IT'S ALL IN THE NOTE
I SENT YOU.

356
00:24:51,423 --> 00:24:56,059
THE TRUTH ABOUT
WHAT MAKES YOU SAD.

357
00:25:03,435 --> 00:25:06,903
<i> [ Boat Departing ]</i>

358
00:25:06,972 --> 00:25:09,439
<i> [ Horn Honks ]</i>

359
00:25:14,113 --> 00:25:18,849
I DOUBT THE BOYS
BACK AT KATIMA BAY ARE SITTIN'
BEACH-SIDE THIS TIME OF YEAR.

360
00:25:18,917 --> 00:25:23,887
PROBABLY FREEZING
THEIR BUTTS OFF ON SOME
FUTILE CAPE-HOPPING S.A.R.

361
00:25:26,725 --> 00:25:32,095
SO, UM, BESIDE THE OBVIOUS,
WHY PULL UP STAKES?

362
00:25:32,163 --> 00:25:34,998
WELL, I WAS FEELING KIND OF
COOPED UP WHERE I WAS LIVING.

363
00:25:35,067 --> 00:25:37,000
SO I DECIDED
TO HEAD OUT WEST.

364
00:25:37,068 --> 00:25:40,336
I INTERVIEWED AT
THE CHANNEL ISLANDS
STATION FIRST,

365
00:25:40,405 --> 00:25:42,906
BUT I DECIDED THAT
THIS WAS THE SPOT FOR ME.

366
00:25:42,974 --> 00:25:45,008
WELL, YOU MADE
THE RIGHT DECISION.

367
00:25:45,077 --> 00:25:47,743
THE CHANNEL ISLANDS
IS FULL OF OUR REJECTS.

368
00:25:47,812 --> 00:25:49,745
THAT'S FUNNY.
HERE YOU GO, SIR.

369
00:25:49,814 --> 00:25:52,415
THEY SAID
THAT THIS GROUP WAS
A BUNCH OF RENEGADES.

370
00:25:52,484 --> 00:25:55,085
THAT'S A CROCK.

371
00:25:55,153 --> 00:25:58,622
THEY SAID GUYS WHO
COULDN'T RESCUE A FISHERMAN
FROM THEIR OWN BAY...

372
00:25:58,690 --> 00:26:01,291
DIDN'T DESERVE
TO WEAR THE UNIFORM.

373
00:26:01,359 --> 00:26:03,326
WERE THEY TALKING ABOUT
THE KING RESCUE?

374
00:26:03,395 --> 00:26:05,995
YES, I THINK THAT WAS
THE NAME THEY USED.

375
00:26:07,433 --> 00:26:11,034
DID SOMETHING GO WRONG?

376
00:26:11,103 --> 00:26:14,670
<i> YOU KNOW, IT'S AMAZING HOW</i>
<i> THE PEOPLE WE PUT OUR LIVES</i>
<i> ON THE LINE FOR...</i>

377
00:26:14,739 --> 00:26:19,175
CAN JUST TURN AROUND
AND SMEAR THE GUARD
WITH ONE NEWS STORY.

378
00:26:19,244 --> 00:26:23,179
<i>THE MAN'S WIFE</i>
<i>TOOK IT HARD.</i>
<i>SHE BLAMED US.</i>

379
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:25,749
I UNDERSTAND HER TRAGEDY.

380
00:26:25,817 --> 00:26:29,218
I GUESS
SHE HAD TO BLAME SOMEBODY,
SO SHE COULD DEAL WITH IT.

381
00:26:29,287 --> 00:26:31,521
<i> I PROMISE YOU.</i>

382
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:34,724
WE DID EVERYTHING WE COULD DO
TO SAVE THAT MAN.

383
00:26:37,563 --> 00:26:39,829
WE DID OUR JOB.

384
00:27:33,785 --> 00:27:35,718
<i>[ Martha ]</i>
<i>PILCHER'S POINT IS WHERE</i>
<i>TOM KING...</i>

385
00:27:35,787 --> 00:27:37,721
<i>WAS KNOWN</i>
<i>TO HAVE BEEN FISHING.</i>

386
00:27:37,789 --> 00:27:40,456
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>THE CURRENT</i>
<i>WAS GOING SOUTHWEST.</i>

387
00:27:40,525 --> 00:27:43,626
<i>[ Martha ] NO ONE WAS SURE</i>
<i>HOW KING'S BOAT WENT DOWN.</i>
<i>NEVER DID FIND IT.</i>

388
00:28:16,661 --> 00:28:18,662
<i>[ Telephone Ringing ]</i>

389
00:28:26,071 --> 00:28:29,505
WHAT? I'M ON MY WAY.

390
00:28:41,085 --> 00:28:43,620
<i> [ Broots ]</i>
<i> IT WASN'T EASY,</i>
<i> BUT I-I HAVE TO ADMIT,</i>

391
00:28:43,689 --> 00:28:46,022
<i> FIGURING JAROD'S MIND</i>
<i> IS A REAL TREAT.</i>

392
00:28:46,090 --> 00:28:48,692
HE'S A DAMN CLEVER GUY.
HE'S A ONE-MAN
SIEGFRIED AND ROY.

393
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:51,060
SHOW ME WHAT YOU HAVE.
OKAY.

394
00:28:53,264 --> 00:28:57,934
WE BACKTRACKED THE CALL
WE THOUGHT WAS COMING
FROM THIS Y.M.C.A....

395
00:28:58,003 --> 00:29:00,604
<i> FROM JAROD'S ROOM--</i>
<i> ROOM 334.</i>

396
00:29:00,672 --> 00:29:05,175
<i> JAROD INTERCONNECTED</i>
<i> 173 INTERNATIONAL CALLS,</i>

397
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:07,777
<i>BUT-BUT BACKTRACKING</i>
<i>THOSE CALLS WAS IMPOSSIBLE...</i>

398
00:29:07,846 --> 00:29:12,315
<i> BECAUSE INSTEAD OF</i>
<i> A CALL-FORWARDING DEVICE</i>
<i> TRIGGERED BY A SINGLE CALL,</i>

399
00:29:12,383 --> 00:29:16,353
<i> ALL 173 CALLS...</i>

400
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:18,688
<i>WERE INDIVIDUALLY INITIATED.</i>

401
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:21,124
INGENIOUS.

402
00:29:21,192 --> 00:29:25,195
<i>[ Broots ] AND A HELL</i>
<i>OF A LOT OF WORK FOR JAROD,</i>
<i>I MIGHT ADD, AND VERY EXPENSIVE.</i>

403
00:29:25,263 --> 00:29:27,163
I DON'T CARE WHAT IT COST.

404
00:29:27,232 --> 00:29:30,800
OH, THAT'S GOOD,
BECAUSE JAROD CHARGED IT
TO YOUR CALLING CARD.

405
00:29:33,538 --> 00:29:36,038
WHERE IS HE?

406
00:29:36,107 --> 00:29:39,709
OH, THE-THE LAST PLACE
WE WOULD EXPECT TO LOOK.

407
00:29:41,613 --> 00:29:44,580
<i> [ Chuckles ]</i>
<i> ROOM 335.</i>
IN THE SAME "Y"?

408
00:29:44,649 --> 00:29:47,283
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>YEAH, IN THE VERY NEXT ROOM.</i>

409
00:30:30,295 --> 00:30:33,863
[ Chuckles ]
GOTCHA.

410
00:30:33,932 --> 00:30:36,499
I FOUND THIS AT
A NOVELTY SHOP ON THE PIER.

411
00:30:36,568 --> 00:30:39,502
YEAH, VERY FUNNY.
JUST WHEN YOU THINK
IT'S YOUR LUCKY DAY,

412
00:30:39,571 --> 00:30:41,938
YOU FIND OUT IT'S NOT.

413
00:30:48,647 --> 00:30:50,714
<i>SO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?</i>

414
00:30:50,783 --> 00:30:54,584
SAME AS YOU.
LOOKING FOR PEACE OF MIND.

415
00:30:54,653 --> 00:30:58,889
AND THE ANSWER TO WHY
SHE'LL NEVER SEE
HER FATHER AGAIN.

416
00:31:05,831 --> 00:31:09,999
- WHO THE HELL ARE YOU, HUH?
- I DON'T REALLY KNOW.

417
00:31:10,068 --> 00:31:12,569
BUT LAST NIGHT I BECAME YOU,

418
00:31:12,638 --> 00:31:15,372
AND I REALIZED
WHY YOU COME HERE SO MUCH,

419
00:31:15,441 --> 00:31:17,641
WHY YOU FEEL SO GUILTY,

420
00:31:17,710 --> 00:31:20,477
AND WHY YOU AND BILSON
DIDN'T SAVE HER FATHER'S LIFE.

421
00:31:20,546 --> 00:31:22,345
WE SEARCHED FOR HIM
FOR TWO DAYS.

422
00:31:22,414 --> 00:31:26,383
BUT YOU MADE SURE THAT
THE SEARCH WAS IN AREAS THAT
YOU KNEW HE WOULDN'T BE FOUND.

423
00:31:26,451 --> 00:31:28,818
YOU COULDN'T AFFORD FOR HIM
TO BE FOUND ALIVE, COULD YOU?

424
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:30,920
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT!

425
00:31:30,989 --> 00:31:34,190
I KNOW YOU AND BILSON MAKE
THE SAME PATROL ON THE SOUTH
SECTOR EVERY TUESDAY NIGHT.

426
00:31:34,259 --> 00:31:37,494
<i>AND EVERY WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON,</i>
<i>YOU MAKE A RATHER</i>
<i>SIZABLE DEPOSIT...</i>

427
00:31:37,563 --> 00:31:40,196
<i>INTO YOUR PRIVATE ACCOUNT</i>
<i>ON CORONADO.</i>

428
00:31:40,265 --> 00:31:43,133
SO WHAT KIND OF CONTRABAND
WERE YOU RUNNING?

429
00:31:43,201 --> 00:31:48,271
- YOU'RE CRAZY, MAN.
- AM I? THE PAINT ON THE HULL.

430
00:31:48,340 --> 00:31:50,940
<i>IT'S GONNA MATCH</i>
<i>THE RESCUE CRUISER THAT</i>
<i>YOU AND BILSON WERE IN...</i>

431
00:31:51,010 --> 00:31:53,844
<i>THE NIGHT THAT HE WENT DOWN.</i>

432
00:31:56,215 --> 00:31:59,950
YOU CAN SEARCH EVERYWHERE
YOU WANT FOR SALVATION.

433
00:32:00,018 --> 00:32:05,355
THE ONLY PLACE
YOU'RE GONNA FIND IT IS IN
THE TRUTH YOU'RE RUNNING FROM.

434
00:32:05,423 --> 00:32:07,357
<i>[ Javi ]</i>
<i>ME AND BILSON MEET</i>
<i>A MEXICAN HAULER...</i>

435
00:32:07,425 --> 00:32:10,427
NAMED THE<i> SANTA MARCA</i>
EVERY TUESDAY NIGHT,

436
00:32:10,495 --> 00:32:12,862
BRINGING IN A SHIPMENT
OF SOMETHING.

437
00:32:12,931 --> 00:32:15,932
I THINK IT'S ROCK,
BUT I'M NOT POSITIVE.

438
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:18,435
WE'RE JUST
PAID DELIVERY BOYS.

439
00:32:21,139 --> 00:32:24,741
I DON'T KNOW HOW
WE HIT HIS BOAT.

440
00:32:24,810 --> 00:32:29,245
I MEAN, IT WAS FOGGY.
I JUST-JUST COULDN'T SEE IT.

441
00:32:29,314 --> 00:32:32,048
BUT WE SHEARED IT
RIGHT IN HALF.

442
00:32:33,885 --> 00:32:36,619
<i> AND THEN--</i>

443
00:32:36,688 --> 00:32:39,089
THEN I SWUNG AROUND AND--

444
00:32:39,157 --> 00:32:41,191
AND I SPOTTED HIM
IN THE WATER.

445
00:32:44,496 --> 00:32:46,429
HE WAS STILL ALIVE.

446
00:32:50,034 --> 00:32:52,034
YEAH.

447
00:32:53,906 --> 00:32:56,639
AND HE LOOKED UP
AT ME, AND--

448
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:00,576
AND ALL I CAN THINK WAS,

449
00:33:00,645 --> 00:33:02,912
"WHAT A SMALL WORLD,"
YOU KNOW?

450
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:07,951
I USED TO SEE HIM
WITH HIS DAUGHTER
AND HIS WIFE AT MASS,

451
00:33:08,019 --> 00:33:10,286
AND I THINK
HE RECOGNIZED ME TOO.

452
00:33:10,355 --> 00:33:13,023
AND THEN HE PUT
HIS HAND UP TO ME.

453
00:33:13,091 --> 00:33:18,028
SO I TRIED
TO PULL HIM ON BOARD,

454
00:33:18,096 --> 00:33:20,096
BUT BILSON STOPPED ME.

455
00:33:22,968 --> 00:33:25,535
HE LITERALLY
PUT A GUN TO MY HEAD
AND TOLD ME TO LEAVE HIM.

456
00:33:25,604 --> 00:33:28,304
- AND IF YOU SAVED HIM--
- THAT WE'D GO TO JAIL.

457
00:33:28,373 --> 00:33:32,242
<i> BUT I'LL TAKE PRISON</i>
<i> IN A HEARTBEAT...</i>

458
00:33:32,310 --> 00:33:34,778
IF I CAN GET OUT OF
THIS HELL I'M IN.

459
00:34:31,202 --> 00:34:34,837
HEY, COULD YOU DO ME A FAVOR?

460
00:34:37,475 --> 00:34:39,409
NOW, THAT'S FUNNY.

461
00:34:39,477 --> 00:34:41,644
I'M SORRY I'M LATE, SIR.

462
00:34:41,713 --> 00:34:43,779
LATE FOR WHAT?
PATROL.

463
00:34:43,848 --> 00:34:45,948
I JUST GOT THE CALL
THIS MORNING
ABOUT RIDING WITH YOU.

464
00:34:46,018 --> 00:34:47,950
RIDING WITH ME?
WHERE'S JAVI?
I DON'T KNOW, SIR.

465
00:34:48,020 --> 00:34:49,952
THEY TOLD ME HE WAS SICK.

466
00:34:50,022 --> 00:34:53,155
SICK?
ACTUALLY, I'M NOT FEELING
VERY WELL MYSELF.

467
00:34:53,224 --> 00:34:56,526
BAD SUSHI.
DO YOU MIND IF I HIT THE HEAD
AND CATCH UP WITH YOU?

468
00:34:56,595 --> 00:34:58,861
NAH, SURE, SURE.

469
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:00,830
IS THERE SOMETHING WRONG?

470
00:35:00,899 --> 00:35:03,032
NO, EVERYTHING'S GREAT.

471
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:05,234
ALL RIGHT.
I WILL SEE YOU IN A MINUTE.

472
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:17,046
- WHERE'S 45?
- I GUESS IT'S ON PATROL.
THE<i> CHRISTI'S--</i>

473
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:19,315
YEAH, PURRING.
I KNOW.

474
00:35:21,987 --> 00:35:24,153
JAVI?

475
00:35:24,222 --> 00:35:26,223
JAVI?

476
00:35:31,330 --> 00:35:34,564
<i>[ Man Over Radio ]</i>
SANTA MARCA<i> TO ROBIN 247.</i>
SANTA MARCA<i> TO ROBIN 247.</i>

477
00:35:34,633 --> 00:35:36,666
COME IN, 247.

478
00:35:36,735 --> 00:35:40,470
ARE YOU INSANE?
WE DON'T HAVE SCHEDULED
RADIO CONTACT UNTIL TONIGHT.

479
00:35:40,539 --> 00:35:42,472
WE'RE CONFIRMING
WE GOT YOUR MESSAGE.

480
00:35:42,541 --> 00:35:44,708
AT YOUR REQUEST, THE RENDEZVOUS
WILL BE AT 10:00 A.M. TODAY.

481
00:35:44,776 --> 00:35:48,745
YOU WILL BE THERE, JAVI?
HELLO? JAVI?

482
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:51,814
RIGHT. TODAY.
I'LL BE THERE.

483
00:35:51,883 --> 00:35:53,884
ADIOS.

484
00:35:58,423 --> 00:36:00,723
WELL, THERE YOU ARE, SIR.

485
00:36:00,792 --> 00:36:02,725
<i> I'M READY IF YOU ARE.</i>

486
00:36:02,794 --> 00:36:05,561
OH, THAT'S ALL RIGHT,
LIEUTENANT.
IT'S-IT'S A ROUTINE PATROL.

487
00:36:05,630 --> 00:36:07,563
<i>I'LL DO IT ALONE.</i>
ARE YOU SURE, SIR?

488
00:36:07,632 --> 00:36:11,334
- YEAH, YEAH.
GO TAKE CARE OF YOUR GUT.
- WELL, THANK YOU, SIR.

489
00:36:18,277 --> 00:36:21,077
YOU DIDN'T TELL US
HE LIVED NEXT DOOR.

490
00:36:21,146 --> 00:36:23,580
YOU DIDN'T ASK.

491
00:36:26,952 --> 00:36:28,952
PAINT.

492
00:36:35,660 --> 00:36:37,260
COME ON.

493
00:36:46,004 --> 00:36:49,038
[ Engine Stalls ]

494
00:36:49,107 --> 00:36:53,876
[ Engine Cranking ]

495
00:36:58,550 --> 00:37:01,985
EXCUSE ME.
HAVE EITHER OF YOU
SEEN THIS MAN?

496
00:37:03,388 --> 00:37:06,155
WELL, THAT'S GREAT.
THAT'S JUST GREAT.

497
00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:08,157
PURRING LIKE
A DAMN KITTEN.

498
00:37:09,894 --> 00:37:13,729
ROBIN 247 TO<i> SANTA MARCA.</i>
COME IN,<i> SANTA MARCA.</i>

499
00:37:31,416 --> 00:37:33,850
RESCUE 45, COME IN.
IS THAT YOU, JAVI?

500
00:37:38,356 --> 00:37:42,692
RESCUE 45, YOU'RE ON
A DIRECT COURSE TO MY CRAFT.
VEER OFF.

501
00:37:44,596 --> 00:37:46,796
RESCUE 45, VEER OFF!

502
00:37:48,032 --> 00:37:52,001
RESCUE 45,
YOU'RE COMING RIGHT AT ME!

503
00:37:52,070 --> 00:37:55,171
RESCUE 45, VEER OFF!

504
00:38:06,618 --> 00:38:08,885
HEY!

505
00:38:12,591 --> 00:38:16,559
- OH, MY GOD!
- WHAT THE HELL'S WRONG
WITH YOU, MAN?

506
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:21,731
- YOU BLIND OR SOMETHIN'?
COME ON! TOSS ME A LINE!
- I CAN'T, SIR.

507
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:25,134
- WHAT?
- I'M SORRY,
BUT I CAN'T RESCUE YOU.

508
00:38:25,202 --> 00:38:27,303
YOU'RE BUCKING FOR
A COURT-MARTIAL, LIEUTENANT!

509
00:38:27,372 --> 00:38:29,171
WELL, THAT IS SERIOUS, SIR.

510
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:33,576
BUT, YOU SEE,
A COURT-MARTIAL,
IT WON'T EXACTLY AFFECT ME.

511
00:38:33,644 --> 00:38:37,646
<i>I'M NOT REALLY A LIEUTENANT.</i>
<i>THE TRUTH IS,</i>

512
00:38:37,715 --> 00:38:39,682
I'M NOT REALLY
IN THE COAST GUARD.

513
00:38:39,751 --> 00:38:41,484
YOU GET ME OUT OF HERE!

514
00:38:41,553 --> 00:38:44,087
OH, DON'T WORRY.
YOU'LL BE OKAY.

515
00:38:44,155 --> 00:38:47,390
MEN HAVE BEEN KNOWN
TO TREAD WATER FOR DAYS.

516
00:38:47,459 --> 00:38:52,028
THIS ISN'T FUNNY!
<i>OH, YOU'RE RIGHT.</i>
<i>IT'S TERRIFYING.</i>

517
00:38:52,097 --> 00:38:54,363
YOU'RE ALL ALONE.

518
00:38:54,432 --> 00:38:57,166
YOU CAN'T SEE ANYTHING
BUT WATER,

519
00:38:57,235 --> 00:38:59,902
AND YOU START THINKING ABOUT
WHAT MIGHT BE DOWN THERE,

520
00:38:59,971 --> 00:39:03,038
<i>WHAT JUST BUMPED YOU</i>
<i>BELOW THE SURFACE.</i>

521
00:39:03,107 --> 00:39:06,742
<i>BUT AFTER A WHILE,</i>
<i>YOUR NERVES WILL SETTLE DOWN.</i>

522
00:39:06,811 --> 00:39:10,579
<i>BUT, UNFORTUNATELY,</i>
<i>THAT'S WHEN YOUR BODY</i>
<i>STARTS TO ACHE,</i>

523
00:39:10,648 --> 00:39:13,850
AND THE ONLY WAY
TO STOP THE PAIN...

524
00:39:13,918 --> 00:39:16,386
IS TO STOP TREADING.

525
00:39:16,455 --> 00:39:19,388
<i>BUT THEN YOU START TO SINK.</i>

526
00:39:19,458 --> 00:39:22,559
<i>AND IN THAT INSTANT</i>
<i>BETWEEN LIFE AND DEATH,</i>

527
00:39:22,627 --> 00:39:26,563
<i>YOU THINK ABOUT</i>
<i>ALL THE PEOPLE AND</i>
<i>ALL THE THINGS YOU LEFT BEHIND.</i>

528
00:39:26,631 --> 00:39:29,431
<i>SO YOU START FIGHTING YOUR WAY</i>
<i>BACK TO THE SURFACE.</i>

529
00:39:29,500 --> 00:39:31,901
YOU FIGHT FOR YOUR LIFE.

530
00:39:31,970 --> 00:39:34,704
YOU CAN'T LEAVE ME HERE!
<i>SURE, I CAN.</i>

531
00:39:34,773 --> 00:39:37,373
JUST LIKE YOU LEFT
TOM KING.

532
00:39:38,610 --> 00:39:41,411
<i> NO!</i>

533
00:39:44,982 --> 00:39:48,250
NO!
[ Gasping ]

534
00:39:50,722 --> 00:39:54,390
<i>EXCUSE ME, SIR.</i>
<i>THERE'S SOMETHING</i>
<i>YOU HAVE TO SEE.</i>

535
00:39:55,627 --> 00:39:58,327
WHAT'S THIS?

536
00:39:58,396 --> 00:40:00,529
<i>[ Javi ]</i>
<i>IT'S THE TRUTH, SIR.</i>

537
00:40:04,169 --> 00:40:07,403
[ Jarod ]
RESCUE UNIT 45 TO BASE.

538
00:40:07,472 --> 00:40:10,839
REQUESTING PICKUP NEAR
D.F. BUOY NUMBER 29.

539
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:16,012
BUT TAKE YOUR TIME
GETTING THERE.
JUST A LITTLE FLOATING DEBRIS.

540
00:40:23,754 --> 00:40:25,688
[ Miss Parker ]
THERE HE IS!

541
00:40:52,217 --> 00:40:54,350
[ Sydney ]
HELLO, JAROD!

542
00:40:54,418 --> 00:40:56,552
HELLO, SYDNEY!

543
00:40:56,621 --> 00:40:59,055
[ Miss Parker ]
GIVE THAT TO ME!

544
00:40:59,124 --> 00:41:00,989
THERE'S NOWHERE
TO GO THIS TIME!

545
00:41:01,058 --> 00:41:05,528
SYDNEY RAISED ME TO BELIEVE
MY MIND CAN TAKE ME ANYWHERE!

546
00:41:21,879 --> 00:41:24,146
[ Engines Stall ]

547
00:41:33,057 --> 00:41:35,024
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>HE'S OUT OF FUEL.</i>

548
00:41:35,093 --> 00:41:40,930
LIKE I TOLD YOU, SYDNEY.
THE SMART ONES
ALWAYS DO SOMETHING STUPID.

549
00:41:43,234 --> 00:41:45,234
GET HIM.

550
00:41:53,378 --> 00:41:56,946
<i> [ Sydney ]</i>
<i> HE'S NOT THERE?</i>
<i> HOW?</i>

551
00:41:57,015 --> 00:42:01,317
I DON'T KNOW.
BUT HE LEFT YOU THIS.

552
00:42:11,095 --> 00:42:14,163
<i> ♪♪ [ Opera ]</i>

553
00:42:19,303 --> 00:42:21,437
HIYA, ROY!
JAROD?

554
00:42:21,506 --> 00:42:24,039
NICE DAY FOR A SWIM!

555
00:42:44,795 --> 00:42:46,762
[ Inaudible ]

556
00:43:36,547 --> 00:43:37,980
[ Clattering ]

557
00:43:38,049 --> 00:43:39,849
WHAT'S THAT, SYDNEY?
I DON'T KNOW.

558
00:43:39,918 --> 00:43:43,685
[ Woman ]
NO! NO!
[ Screaming, Sobbing ]

559
00:43:43,754 --> 00:43:46,255
THEY'RE TRYING TO HURT HER!
STAY HERE, JAROD.

560
00:43:46,323 --> 00:43:48,223
NO!
[ Man ]
GET HER ON THE ELEVATOR!

561
00:43:48,292 --> 00:43:50,826
<i> [ Young Jarod ]</i>
<i> STOP IT!</i>
<i> [ Gunshot ]</i>

562
00:43:50,894 --> 00:43:52,929
[ Man ]
GET THE KID OUT OF HERE!
STOP!

563
00:43:52,997 --> 00:43:56,532
<i> [ Gunfire ]</i>

564
00:43:56,600 --> 00:44:00,603
[ Girl Screaming ] MAMA!
NO, KEEP HER BACK!
KEEP HER BACK!

565
00:44:00,671 --> 00:44:04,039
- [ Young Jarod ]
LEAVE ME ALONE!
-<i> NO! MAMA!</i>

566
00:44:04,108 --> 00:44:05,708
[ Sobbing ]

567
00:44:41,879 --> 00:44:44,580
IT'S ME.

568
00:44:44,649 --> 00:44:47,850
I WANNA KNOW WHAT
REALLY HAPPENED TO MY MOM.

569
00:44:59,831 --> 00:45:02,364
THANKS, ROY.
IT AIN'T NOTHIN'.

570
00:45:04,936 --> 00:45:08,171
MAGDELINE'S
OUT THERE SOMEWHERE.

571
00:45:08,239 --> 00:45:10,173
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

572
00:45:10,241 --> 00:45:12,241
I THINK I'LL TAKE A WALK.

573
00:45:18,582 --> 00:45:23,252
THANK YOU.
HOW ABOUT YOU?

574
00:45:23,321 --> 00:45:25,354
I THINK I'LL TAKE A DRIVE.

575
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:28,591
<i>[ Cheering ]</i>

576
00:45:31,963 --> 00:45:35,230
<i>[ Man Over P.A. ]</i>
<i>GENTLEMEN, START YOUR ENGINES!</i>

577
00:45:38,169 --> 00:45:40,102
OKAY, JAROD,
YOU'RE SET.

578
00:46:11,268 --> 00:46:12,334
[ Mews ]

